According to this article the rise in prices is largely due to a reduction in supply thanks to the pandemic. Apparently much of the natural gas production is in association with oil, and oil production has dropped with oil prices. Based on that I think there's a good chance that this could revert to the original trend somewhat by June, meaning lower prices.

Over last 9 years, comparison of June prices with previous December : -> June prices have been higher than previous December 4 out of 9 times. -> Only once they were higher by more than 15% -> In 3 years they were higher by maximum of 6.1% -> Rest of the time they were lower than December (average 5% below December prices).
